<font color="#FF0000">THE COALS OF YOUTH</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jan 21 22:03:10 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
    Then, the flames burned so brightly with the heat of life and death.<br><br>
   We were all young then and God help us, with death so near, we knew that we were really alive.   Perhaps the memories of Viet Nam are the only coals of passion that still have the heat to warm us. <br><br>
    Thus as the clouds gather and the days grow shorter---we huddle closer to the dying heat, hoping to re-capture that passon and hold off the long cold night.   <br>
  <br>
&quot;All the brothers are valant, and all the sisters vituous.&quot;
